\int{\sec^{n}(\theta)}d\theta=\frac{\tan(\theta)\sec^{n-2}(\theta)}{n-1}-\frac{n-2}{n-1}\int{\sec^{n-2}(\theta)d\theta}
=\sec^{n-2}x\tan x-\int\left((n-2)\sec^{n-3}x(\sec x\tan x)\cdot \tan x\right)dx 
=\sec^{n-2}x\tan x-(n-2)\int\sec^{n-2}x(\sec^2x-1)dx 
C
=\sec^{n-2}x\tan x-(n-2)\int\sec^nxdx+(n-2)\int\sec^{n-2}xdx+C 
\implies (1+n-2)\sec^nxdx=\sec^{n-2}x\tan x+(n-2)\int\sec^{n-2}xdx+C
\tan^2 (\theta)+1=\sec^2(\theta)
\sec^n \theta=\sec^{n-2} \theta \cdot \sec^2 \theta=\sec^{n-2}\theta \cdot (\tan^2 \theta+1)
\int{\sec^{n}(\theta)}d\theta= \int{\sec^{n-2}(\theta)} \sec^2(\theta) d\theta
d(\tan \theta) = \frac{d\theta}{\cos^2\theta} = \sec^2 \theta d\theta
\int \frac{d\theta}{\cos^n \theta}
